{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1775049295,"nonce":"QxyMCtXRKM2USI5s+ZZ57qck5Ic=","title":"render_markdown does not sanitize link protocols","message":"render_markdown in ApplicationHelper uses Redcarpet with filter_html: true, which strips raw HTML tags but does not filter dangerous link protocols. Markdown like [click](javascript:alert(1)) renders into an unsafe \u003ca href\u003e value.\n\nThis affects all pages that render user-editable markdown content:\n- /ausleihbedingungen (TOS)\n- /datenschutz (privacy policy)\n- /impressum (imprint)\n- Self-registration page (embedded TOS)\n\nCurrent risk is low because content is authored by authenticated admins only (requires can :edit, LegalText). But the helper should be hardened regardless.\n\nOptions:\n- Enable Redcarpet's safe_links_only option to block javascript:/vbscript:/data: protocols\n- Or sanitize the rendered HTML with Rails sanitize() and an allowlist\n- Or both","files":null}]}